<item>
            <title>[FELIX-2093] iPOJO doesn&apos;t always use the correct class loader</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-2093</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There are appears to be an issue with nullable object creation, where iPOJO uses the wrong class loader to generate the nullable object for an optional service dependency and this results in the component never getting created. The exact details are a little sketchy to me, but I have shown the example to Clement and he can fill in the details.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12456619">FELIX-2093</key>
            <summary>iPOJO doesn&apos;t always use the correct class loader</summary>
