                                    <component>iPOJO</component>
                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>0</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12835153" author="clement.escoffier" created="Thu, 18 Feb 2010 09:22:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue comes from the classloader used to create the Nullable object (dynamic proxy). &lt;br/&gt;
Currently, we use the bundle classloader which is not necessary correct because it cannot resolve classes used by the service interface that are not imported (the basic solution is to import them).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using the service interface classloader will fix this issue but break the Nullable interface support (which allows the implementation to detect if the object is a Nullable or not).  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12836347" author="clement.escoffier" created="Sun, 21 Feb 2010 09:45:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed at revision 912323.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
